context: Illustrated humour periodicals were popular in 19th-century Britain, the earliest of which was the short-lived <a0_0><b5_0>The Glasgow Looking Glass<b5_0/><a0_0/> in <a1_0><b6_0>1825<b6_0/><a1_0/>. On occasion the cartoons in these magazines appeared in sequences; the character <a3_0><b8_0>Ally Sloper<b8_0/><a3_0/> featured in the earliest serialized comic strip when the character began to feature in its own weekly magazine in <a4_0><b9_0>1884<b9_0/><a4_0/>.
